'''WLKE''' (99.1 [[FM broadcasting|FM]]) is an American [[radio station]] broadcasting a [[country music]] format. Licensed to [[Bar Harbor, Maine]], USA, the station serves the Northern and Downeast Maine area. The station is currently owned by [[Blueberry Broadcasting]] and features programing from [[Premiere Radio Networks]].<ref> {{cite web|url=http://www.fcc.gov/fcc-bin/fmq?call=WLKE |title=WLKE Facility Record |work=United States [[Federal Communications Commission]], audio division }}</ref>
==History== The station was assigned [[call sign]] WPRG on March 24, 1988. On May 19, 1992, the station changed its call sign to the current WLKE.<ref> {{cite web|url=http://fjallfoss.fcc.gov/cgi-bin/ws.exe/prod/cdbs/pubacc/prod/call_hist.pl?Facility_id=62289&Callsign=WLKE |title=WLKE Call Sign History |work=United States [[Federal Communications Commission]], audio division }}</ref> As of September 28th, 2009, it became part of a three station country network based out of Blueberry's Bangor office, simulcasting [[WBFB]] and also heard on [[WMCM]].<ref>http://www.fybush.com/NERW/2009/090928/nerw.html#me][http://knox.villagesoup.com/Community/story.cfm?StoryID=177087</ref>
